title: New Block Title
body:
Once you have downloaded the TCPR Link app, you need to pair it with your CPRcard using a bluetooth connection.

When you open the app, you will automatically be guided through a one-time pairing process to establish a bluetooth connection between your phone and the CPRcard.

If you have not received a CPRcard yet, you will not be able to use the TCPR Link app.  Please go through the e-learning without having the CPRcard to learn how to use the TCPR Link system.  Once you receive the CPRcard you will be able to conduct the pairing and try the app.
instruction: If you have not already paired the app with the card, watch this video or follow the step-by-step guide below.

title: New Block Title
body:
After the initial pairing you are now ready to use TCPR Link for both practice and treatment.

Below is an example of the chain of events that happens when you receive a myResponder alert.

Note that when you arrive at the scene the bystander has already called the 995 and is talking to the dispatcher.  After opening the TCPR Link app, you press “995” and establish contact with a another dispatcher at 995, who will coach you in what to do.

title: 995 dispatcher's role
body:
When you do CPR on a patient, CPRcard measures the compression quality and streams the data to the TCPR Link app via Bluetooth. TCPR Link app streams the data to the cloud. The dispatcher can see your CPR quality and video, and use this to coach you to do good CPR.  The dispatcher might ask you to get help from someone to place or hold the the camera in a good position to see the patient's chest. This helps the dispatcher to guide you to perform CPR with good technique.   

Make sure you can the see the CPR feedback on the mobile device during CPR.

Below is an example of the feedback in TCPR Link system during CPR and the data and video which the dispatcher is using during coaching.

title: Component
body: Turn on the CPRcard by pinching the power button for a few seconds until you see lights starts blinking. Place the card near your smartphone, while the bluetooth connection is established. To complete the pairing, find the serial number on the front of the card and enter the 3 digits.

title: Avoid leaning
body: Remember to release completely between each compression to allow the chest to recoil and the blood to return to the heart as seen here. This will also help you achieve your target depth.
